# Project Page — Content Requirements Brief

> **Purpose**: This document is a handoff guide for **designers**, **content managers**, and **marketers**. It lists every piece of content (text, image, video) required to populate a single project detail page on the website. It also includes a CMS-ready data schema so the backend team knows exactly what fields to create.

---

## CMS Data Schema (Per Project)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Every project is a **single content entry** in the CMS. The schema below maps 1:1 to the [ProjectDetail](file:///Users/metwally/Desktop/Kimi_Agent_Clone%20Hello%20Monday%20Site%202/nextjs-app/src/lib/project-catalog.ts#45-61) TypeScript type used in the frontend code. When building the CMS, replicate these fields exactly.

### Top-Level Fields

| Field | Type | Required | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| [id](file:///Users/metwally/Desktop/Kimi_Agent_Clone%20Hello%20Monday%20Site%202/nextjs-app/src/components/LiquidCard.tsx#146-304) | Slug | ✅ | URL-safe unique ID | `google-gemini-competition` |
| `title` | Short Text | ✅ | Full project title (Client — Tagline) | `Google — Gemini Developer Competition` |
| `tags` | Multi-Select | ✅ | Category labels | `Experiences`, `Branding`, `Platform`, `Products`, `E-commerce` |
| `image` | Image | ✅ | Primary card thumbnail (used on homepage grid) | 1920×1080 JPG |
| `aspectRatio` | Enum | ✅ | Card shape on homepage: `portrait`, `landscape`, `square` | `landscape` |

### Hero Section

| Field | Type | Required | Description | Spec for Designer |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `heroLabel` | Short Text | ✅ | Eyebrow text above hero title | _"Case Study"_ or _"Google / Launch Experience"_ |
| `heroTitle` | Short Text | ✅ | The massive hero headline | Max ~4 words. Will be split into per-character animation |
| `heroSubtitle` | Short Text | ✅ | Sub-headline below hero title | 1 sentence, ~15 words max |
| `heroSummary` | Long Text | ❌ | Internal summary (SEO meta description) | 1–2 sentences |

### Intro Meta Bar (Overview Strip)

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `introMeta.launchLabel` | Short Text | ✅ | CTA button text (e.g., "Launch project", "Visit site") |
| `introMeta.type` | Short Text | ✅ | Project type label |
| `introMeta.client` | Short Text | ✅ | Client name |
| `introMeta.deliverables` | Short Text | ✅ | Comma-separated deliverable list |

### Overview Facts (4 items)

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `overview[].label` | Short Text | ✅ | Fact label (e.g., "Client", "Timeline") |
| `overview[].value` | Short Text | ✅ | Fact value (e.g., "Google", "6 weeks") |

> [!TIP]
> Recommended labels: **Client**, **Scope/Program**, **Deliverables**, **Timeline**

### Editorial Intro (2 paragraphs)

| Field | Type | Required | Description | Word Count |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `intro[0]` | Long Text | ✅ | Opening paragraph — sets the story context | 40–60 words |
| `intro[1]` | Long Text | ✅ | Second paragraph — design approach or insight | 30–50 words |

### Primary Showcase Image

| Field | Type | Required | Spec for Designer |
|---|---|---|---|
| `primaryShowcase.src` | Image | ✅ | **Hero image**: 2400×1200px minimum, 2:1 or 4:3 aspect ratio, JPG/WebP |
| `primaryShowcase.alt` | Short Text | ✅ | Accessible description |
| `primaryShowcase.label` | Short Text | ❌ | Internal label |

### Process Steps (4 items)

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `process[].phase` | Short Text | ✅ | Phase number: "01", "02", "03", "04" |
| `process[].label` | Short Text | ✅ | Phase name: e.g., "Discovery", "Design", "Build", "Launch" |
| `process[].desc` | Long Text | ✅ | 1-sentence description of what happened during that phase |

### Story Chapters (3 sections recommended)

Each chapter is a **repeatable block** in the CMS:

| Field | Type | Required | Spec |
|---|---|---|---|
| `sections[].eyebrow` | Short Text | ✅ | Category label: "Challenge", "System/Interface", "Outcome" |
| `sections[].title` | Short Text | ✅ | Chapter headline, ~8–12 words |
| `sections[].body[]` | Long Text (list) | ✅ | 2 paragraphs, ~30–40 words each |
| `sections[].image` | Image | ✅ | **Chapter image**: 1600×2000px (portrait) or 1600×1400px. JPG/WebP |
| `sections[].imageAlt` | Short Text | ✅ | Accessible image description |
| `sections[].imageLayout` | Enum | ✅ | `"left"` or `"right"` — alternates per chapter |
| `sections[].tone` | Enum | ❌ | `"light"` (default) or `"navy"` (dark background) |

### Impact Metrics (3 items)

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `impactMetrics[].label` | Short Text | ✅ | The headline metric (e.g., "3,000+ Apps", "40% Increase") |
| `impactMetrics[].value` | Short Text | ✅ | Supporting context (e.g., "Submissions received", "In engagement") |

### Visual Gallery (4–6 images)

| Field | Type | Required | Spec for Designer |
|---|---|---|---|
| `gallery[].src` | Image | ✅ | **Gallery image**: 2400×1350px (16:9), JPG/WebP |
| `gallery[].alt` | Short Text | ✅ | Description |
| `gallery[].label` | Short Text | ❌ | Internal label |

### Testimonials (2–3 items)

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `testimonials[].quote` | Long Text | ✅ | Client/stakeholder quote, 1–2 sentences |
| `testimonials[].author` | Short Text | ✅ | Person's name |
| `testimonials[].role` | Short Text | ✅ | Title/role |

### Color Palette (3–5 swatches)

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `colors[].hex` | Short Text | ✅ | Hex code (e.g., `#0a1b3f`) |
| `colors[].name` | Short Text | ✅ | Friendly name (e.g., "Deep Navy") |

### Credits (3–5 entries)

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `credits[].label` | Short Text | ✅ | Role (e.g., "Strategy", "Design", "Motion", "Build") |
| `credits[].value` | Short Text | ✅ | Description (e.g., "Launch narrative", "UI + art direction") |

### Related Projects

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `relatedIds` | Reference (multi) | ✅ | 2–3 project references |

---

## Image & Video Asset Specifications

### Summary Table

| Asset | Count per project | Min Resolution | Aspect Ratio | Format | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Card Thumbnail | 1 | 1920×1080 | 16:9 or 4:3 | JPG/WebP | Used on homepage grid |
| Primary Showcase | 1 | 2400×1200 | 2:1 or 4:3 | JPG/WebP | Full-width cinematic |
| Chapter Images | 3 | 1600×2000 | ~4:5 portrait | JPG/WebP | Alternating L/R layout |
| Gallery Images | 4–6 | 2400×1350 | 16:9 | JPG/WebP | Horizontal scroll strip |
| **Total images** | **9–11** | | | | |

> [!NOTE]
> **Video (optional future CMS field)**: If a project has a video hero or demo reel, provide a 1080p MP4 (max 30s, <10MB) or embed URL (Vimeo/YouTube). The frontend can be extended to support `heroVideo` and `showcaseVideo` fields.

### Image Quality Guidelines for Designers

- **No text baked into images** — all text is rendered by the frontend.
- **Consistent color grading** — images should feel cohesive within a single project.
- **People/devices are okay** — but avoid heavy watermarks or logos unless intentional.
- **Optimize for web** — target <300KB per image after compression. Use `squoosh.app` or `tinypng.com`.

---

## Content Writing Guide (For Content Managers & Marketers)

### Tone of Voice
- **Confident but not boastful** — let the work speak.
- **Editorial, not promotional** — think magazine feature, not ad copy.
- **Third person** — "We designed…" or "The team crafted…"
- **Present tense for outcomes** — "The page becomes the template…"

### Per-Section Writing Prompts

| Section | Prompt to answer | Target length |
|---|---|---|
| `heroTitle` | What is the project's memorable name? | 2–4 words |
| `heroSubtitle` | What was the deliverable or experience type? | ~10 words |
| `intro[0]` | What was the client's need and the project context? | 40–60 words |
| `intro[1]` | What was the design approach or creative strategy? | 30–50 words |
| Chapter 1 "Challenge" | What problem did the team solve? | 2 paragraphs × 30 words |
| Chapter 2 "System" | What design/technical system was built? | 2 paragraphs × 30 words |
| Chapter 3 "Outcome" | What was the final result and its impact? | 2 paragraphs × 30 words |
| `impactMetrics` | 3 quantifiable or qualitative results | Label: 2–3 words, Value: 2–4 words |
| `testimonials` | Real client feedback (or paraphrased with permission) | 1–2 sentences each |
| `process` | Brief description of each phase | 1 sentence each |

---

## Per-Project Content Checklist

Use this checklist for **each of the 23 projects** when collecting content:

```
PROJECT: ___________________________

□ Card thumbnail image (1920×1080)
□ Primary showcase image (2400×1200)
□ 3 chapter images (1600×2000 each)
□ 4–6 gallery images (2400×1350 each)
□ Hero title (2–4 words)
□ Hero subtitle (~10 words)
□ Hero summary (1–2 sentences, for SEO)
□ Client name
□ Project type/tags
□ Deliverables list
□ Timeline (e.g., "6 weeks", "3 months")
□ CTA button text (e.g., "Launch project")
□ 2 intro paragraphs
□ 3 story chapters (eyebrow + title + 2 paragraphs each)
□ 3 impact metrics (label + value)
□ 4 process steps (phase, label, description)
□ 2–3 testimonial quotes (quote + author + role)
□ 3–5 color palette swatches (hex + name)
□ 3–5 credits (role + description)
□ 2–3 related project references
□ Optional: video hero (MP4 or embed URL)
□ Optional: live project URL for CTA
```

