## CMS Migration Notes

When migrating to a headless CMS (e.g., Sanity, Strapi, Contentful, Hygraph):

1. **Content Type**: Create a [Project](file:///Users/metwally/Desktop/Kimi_Agent_Clone%20Hello%20Monday%20Site%202/nextjs-app/src/components/sections/Projects.tsx#137-227) content type with all fields above.
2. **Repeatable Blocks**: `sections`, `gallery`, `testimonials`, `process`, `colors`, `credits`, `overview`, `impactMetrics` should all be **repeatable component/block** fields.
3. **References**: `relatedIds` should be a **reference field** pointing to other [Project](file:///Users/metwally/Desktop/Kimi_Agent_Clone%20Hello%20Monday%20Site%202/nextjs-app/src/components/sections/Projects.tsx#137-227) entries.
4. **Media**: All image fields should use the CMS's built-in media library with focal point cropping.
5. **Enums**: `aspectRatio` (`portrait`/`landscape`/`square`), `imageLayout` (`left`/`right`), `tone` (`light`/`navy`) should be dropdown selects.
6. **Slug**: Auto-generate from `title`, allow manual override.
7. **Preview**: Set up a preview URL pointing to `/projects/[slug]` for live previewing.
